<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">
Features
</Paragraph>

<List Margin="25,0,0,0">
<ListItem><Paragraph>Utility functions include normal distribution, F-distribution, and T-distribution.</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>


<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">
Interactive Features</Paragraph>


<List Margin="25,0,0,0">

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The <Bold>Distribution</Bold> combo box includes a list of available utility functions.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The <Bold>Probability</Bold> combo box sets the probability value.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The <Bold>N Degree of Freedom</Bold> combo box sets the N degree of freedom.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The <Bold>M Degree of Freedom</Bold> combo box sets the M degree of freedom.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The <Bold>IsInversed</Bold> check box gets the inversed value of the utility functions.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The <Bold>Value</Bold> text displays the result of the utility test performed for the chart.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>

</List>
